# Project: Document Search (Intellectible take-home)

Build a PDF document search feature: drag-drop PDFs, hybrid search across them, results with
citations, a draft collection panel. ~3 hour prototype. Code must be readable and defensible
to technical founders, so favour clarity over cleverness and comment the retrieval logic.

## Stack
- Next.js, App Router, single repo, TypeScript.
- Backend via Next.js API routes. No separate Python service.
- Supabase: Postgres + pgvector for chunks/embeddings, Supabase Storage for PDFs.
- All model calls via OpenRouter (OpenAI-compatible client, base url
  https://openrouter.ai/api/v1). Read OPENROUTER_API_KEY from env. Never hardcode keys.

## Architecture (keep the RAG pipeline as separate, commented modules)
- parse: extract per-page text (unpdf or pdf.js). Preserve page numbers.
- chunk: ~500-800 token chunks with overlap. Tag each chunk {docId, page}.
- embed: batch chunks to OpenRouter /embeddings, model openai/text-embedding-3-small
  (1536 dims). The pgvector column dimension must match.
- index: store vectors in pgvector; build a Postgres full-text index on the same chunks.
- search: hybrid. Vector cosine + full-text, combined with reciprocal rank fusion. Return
  snippet + source doc + page.

## Async
- Upload returns immediately. The document row carries a status: processing -> ready.
- The frontend polls status. Show per-document progress.

## Draft feature
- "Add to draft" collects passages with their citations in a side panel.
- Optional generate step: send only the collected passages + a prompt to an OpenRouter chat
  model, draft one paragraph, preserve citations. Strictly grounded in the passages, no
  outside model knowledge.

## Out of scope (do not build; leave a short comment where it would go)
OCR, table extraction, real queue infra, multi-tenant isolation, rerank. Rerank may be
written behind a flag only if explicitly asked.

## Conventions
- Readable over clever. Short comments on the retrieval logic so each module can be
  explained out loud.
- Strong UI states: empty, uploading/parsing, ready, results, draft. The prototype should
  feel good to use.
- UI copy: direct, no corporate filler, no AI slop. No em dashes.
- Do not commit secrets. Env for all keys.
